SUMMARY:kr8: Kubernetes Configuration Management
ORGANIZER:Lee Briggs
CATEGORIES:talk
DTSTAMP:20181228T000000Z
DTSTART:20190205T163000Z
DTEND:20190205T172500Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>The abstraction layer for Configuration Management is moving away from the operating system to the orchestration layer,
but the configuration management tools aren&rsquo;t keeping up.<br />
As the number of Kubernetes clusters you run grows,
your ability to install components on them with slight and subtle differences becomes more and more manual.</p>

<p>kr8 is designed to take the heavy lifting out of this,
by allowing you to manipulate yaml with a first class data templating language (jsonnet) without all the overhead of similar tools.<br />
It follows the principles of simplicity you&rsquo;d expect from a bunch of admins writing a tool,
while still allowing the power and flexibility to get what you need done.</p>

<p>This talk will go over the inspiration behind kr8,
as well as show a practical demo and example of deploying the components
you choose to multiple clusters with the modifications needed in a few lines of code.</p>

